def: Used to the way; broken. [R.]A horse that is not well wayed; he starts at every bird that fliesout the hedge. Selden.
Living in the earth; -- applied to the ground beetles.
Gain; advantage; profit.That thy profiting may appear to all. 1 Tim. iv. 15.
The movement caused in the sensory organs by external agentsand transmitted to the muscles by the nerves. Dunglison.

The way in which the parts of anything are put together; often,the way in which an actor is dressed, painted, etc., in personating acharacter.The unthinking masses are necessarily teleological in their mentalmake-up. L. F. Ward.
Designating a light and elegant style developed in Englandunder George III., chiefly by Messrs. A.Heppelwhite & Co.
Ornamented; decorated; esp., embroidered on the edges. Purfledwork (Arch.), delicate tracery, especially in Gothic architecture.
The process of laminating, or the state of being laminated.
A sort of pneumonia occuring in iron workers, produced by theinhalation of particles of iron.
